    <div class="rightSection" id="reboxing">
        <p1>
            <h2>Re-Packaging</h2>
            Before re-boxing, some items need to be put in bubble bags or foam bags to protect them from damage in handling.
            <ul>
                <li>Each joycon must be placed inside of a small bubble bag.</li>
                <li>Each 3DS console, HAC console, or HDH console must be placed inside of a foam bag.</li>
                <li>These are rare, but WiiU Consoles and Game Pads must be placed into a large bubble bag.</li>
                <li>Other accessories such as cables/chargers may be loose in the box.</li>
                <li>Game Cards and other small items should be affixed to the top of the inside of the box inside of a UPS bag.</li>
            </ul>
            Depending on the items contained in the package, we must rebox them accordingly along with <u>all</u> of the corresponding paperwork, letters, shipping labels, etc.:
            <ul>
                <li>If there are only JoyCons in a package, place them inside of the small sized box.
                    <br>The Small Box can fit up to 4 joycons. Do not include more than 4 joycons in this box </li>
                <li>There is a medium-sized box which is sometimes used in place of the small sized box, for joycon-only ROs, HDH consoles, or 3DS consoles.
                    <br>The medium-sized box can fit up to 6 joycons, or 1 3DS/HDH console. If the HDH console includes accessories, use a larger box than this.</li>
                <li>The larger sized box should primarily be used for HAC consoles with accessories. Occasionally, we receive a WiiU Console or gamepad which should also be packaged in the large box.</li>
                <li>On rare occasions, we may receive a WiiU Console with a Gamepad. These should be packaged in the extra-large "Overpack" box.</li>
            </ul>
        </p1>
    </div>
